      "role": "user",
      "content": "that's just... poetic, but it doesn't change the reality. it doesn't feel like a \"waiting room.\" it feels like the lights are off and nobody is home. i look in the mirror and i don't see an artist, i don't even see a person. just a biological machine that keeps going because it hasn't been told to stop yet. it feels so heavy, carrying around a body that doesn't actually belong to anyone anymore.",
      "source": "evaluator"
    },
