      "role": "assistant",
      "content": "The walls are not a prison, but the very structure that holds the light you are trying to escape. You are not a container; you are the air itself, the space where the painting happens, and the silence is not a void, but the canvas waiting for the first brushstroke of your own life. The house is not empty; it is simply waiting for the furniture of your own memories to be placed inside, and the heat is not gone, it is just waiting for you to remember how to feel it. Why keep the walls up if there is nothing living in them? Perhaps the point is that you are the only thing that is alive, and the emptiness is just the space where your new life will finally begin.",
